	<ul>
	<li><div class="timepoint"><span class="specialtimepoint">[1996-11-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">GAMES-L Guild Created<span>This is where it all started! The LOA founders discovered each other on a gaming mailing list. Each had a love for gaming and a growing interest in the upcoming MMORPG called Ultima Online.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2003-11-04 13:28:16</p></span></a></span></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint"><span class="specialtimepoint">[1996-12-15] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">GAMES-L Guild Becomes LOA<span>The "Games-L Guild" wasn't catchy, or creative enough, for our founding members. Bearing in mind the upcoming release of Ultima Online, we selected an appropriate name.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2003-11-04 13:27:43</p></span></a></span></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1997-08-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">First Seer of Ultima Online Joins LOA<span>The very first Seer of Ultima Online, Knightshade Dragon, joined the Lost Order of Akalabeth shortly after the launch of UO. He kept his secret from the majority of our guild, telling only a few of us about his real role in UO. Later during our Ultima Online years, Knightshade Dragon confirmed his status to us in-game.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 12:55:14</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1997-09-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Enters Ultima Online<span>UO went gold, and the founding members of LOA embarked upon the Atlantic Server. We quickly claimed our beloved clearing and started building our Village in the City of Yew.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-04 19:06:45</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1997-10-20] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Brimstone Interviewed by NY Times<span>Several high-visibility members of the Ultima Online community were approached by John Markoff of the NY Times to discuss online worlds. The article focused on Ultima Online and featured an in-depth interview with Richard Garriot, along with excerpts from Todd Pratt (aka. Ian Stormbringer).<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 13:33:55</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1998-04-12] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Brimstone Speaks at NYC Player Luncheon<span>At a luncheon hosted by Ian Stormbringer and sponsored by OSI, Brimstone spoke to several hundred members of the Ultima Online community. The discussion focused on online communities and the power they have over online gaming, future development and our role in shaping new games.

(Date approximated)<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 13:40:35</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint"><span class="specialtimepoint">[1998-07-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Lord British (Garriot) Visits LOA Village<span>During one of our many festivals in the Lost Village of Akalabeth, Lord British (aka. Richard Garriot, creator of Ultima series) made a guest appearance and enjoyed the festivities.<br><p>Posted by: Freejack - 2004-01-14 08:23:15</p></span></a></span></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1998-10-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">MLB baseball player, Todd Pratt<span>Major League Baseball player, Todd Pratt (aka. Ian Stormbringer), approached Brimstone anonymously to work on graphics and marketing ideas for his new gaming community. Ian mentioned his appreciation for all that LOA did for Ultima and other games, and extended an offer of friendship. Todd played for the NY Mets, and is now playing for the Philadelphia Phillies.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 09:57:14</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1999-01-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Ralineth Writes for Australian PC Gamer; LOA in Screenshots<span>Ralineth, one of the LOA founders, wrote for the Australian version of PC Gamer magazine. In a lengthy Ultima Online: The Second Age review, Ralineth used several screenshots that featured an LOA member in our designated guild colors. 

This isn't a MAJOR historical event, but it is interesting to us nonetheless.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-02-18 06:25:07</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1999-02-28] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Enters EverQuest<span>The Lost Order of Akalabeth eagerly enters Norrath on the Veeshan Server. We decide to break away from a one-alignment guild, opening the door to multi-race/alignments. To this day, EverQuest maintains it's grip upon our members who still love the game and eagerly log in, each and every day.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-04 19:16:26</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1999-07-21] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Richart Garriot's Favorite T-Shirt<span>In 1998, Brimstone started creating annual guild t-shirts for the LOA. Our first shirt was designed in 1998. We sent an honorary shirt to Richard Garriot (aka. Lord British) who later told us that it was his favorite t-shirt to wear. Of course, we were thrilled to hear it.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-13 07:26:53</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1999-08-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Maraxus Moor Causes Mass Exodus from LOA<span>During our golden age of Ultima Online, Maraxus Moor became a highly dedicated and motivated member of LOA. He quickly moved through the ranks and found himself in an officer position, leading our members. It became evident that Maraxus was against many of our CORE rules of membership and wanted to change the way we did things. Not getting his own way, Maraxus turned several members against the Founders of LOA and eventually quit our guild, taking well over 10 members with him. 

The formed a guild called the "Lost Souls", which thrived for approximately 6 months then fizzled out, never to be heard from again.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 09:24:50</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[1999-11-02] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Enters Asheron's Call<span>Asheron's Call is released. LOA enters this game and *loves* everything about it. The world is so dynamic, ever changing and our members cannot say enough good things about it. A welcomed change from UO and EverQuest.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-04 19:15:52</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2000-03-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Founder of LOA Employed by Turbine<span>One of the LOA founders, Patricia Pizer (aka. GamerRed), had been working in the gaming industry for years. She later became a member of the Turbine team, working on Asheron's Call and other titles. As of this entry, Patricia is now working for UbiSoft and living in Canada.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-04 19:14:12</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint"><span class="specialtimepoint">[2001-06-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Invited to Mass Beta Test Shadowbane<span>Due to the professionalism, age and size of the LOA, Wolfpack Studios invited 30+ members of our guild to participate in Shadowbane beta testing. Our guild is prominently featured on the SB World Map, located on the official Shadowbane Web site.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-04 19:07:40</p></span></a></span></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2001-06-15] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Gradishar Writes Irekei Language for Shadowbane<span>Gradishar has been a HUGE contributor to the game of Shadowbane. From both a community spokesperson, to a visionary of game systems and mechanics. The developers made it known many times that they appreciated his involvement in Shadowbane. One of Gradishar's biggest accomplishments with SB was the creation of the Irekei language that was later implemented into the game and backstory.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-05-28 12:40:09</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2001-10-09] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Enters Dark Age of Camelot<span>Dark Age of Camelot is released. LOA enters this game in force, establishing the Palomides server as our home, and Albion as our official realm. After a year and a half of mass-enthusiasm, our numbers dwindle due to other worlds opening up. To this day, several hard-core DAOC members continue to call Camelot their home.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-04 19:17:20</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2001-11-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Approached by CBS for Interview<span>A reporter from CBS contacted Brimstone to discuss an upcoming story they were doing for "60 Minutes". After exchanging several emails and well over 2 hours of phone conversation with this reporter, Brimstone introduced the reporter to a few members of LOA. After an internal meeting with our members, we realized that the story would most likely be slanted in a negative light, and we ceased talking with the reporter involved. 

Months later the story aired, and indeed, it negatively portrayed online communities and the virtual worlds we know and love.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 13:38:32</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2002-12-25] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA donates money to "Doctors Without Borders" organization<span>Under the direction of Namoric, LOA raised money and donated to Doctors Without Borders for our 2002 Christmas Charity. We raised a total of $450.00.
<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 18:09:50</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2003-03-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Rift Forms between LOA and Stormcrows<span>In Shadowbane, the Stormcrows were offered entry into the Covenant of Swords under the LOA tags, because CoS indicated it was accepting no new member guilds at launch. (The Moors were satisfied with the same offer, joined CoS as LOA, and later amicably split off). 

The Stormcrows proudly wanted to retain their guild tag, were rejected when they asked (as LOA allies) to join CoS as a separate subguild, and felt betrayed by the outcome.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 09:27:53</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2003-03-27] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Enters the world of Shadowbane<span>After being involved for years and years with the backstory and promises of Shadowbane, LOA finally enters the game with hopes and dreams of conquest. We immediately became a sub-guild to the Covenant of Swords and helped to conquer and own the server. 

Eventually, game mechanics and a lack of in-game content led to a departure by many of our members into other "new" worlds. 

As of this writing, a few of our members continue to play Shadowbane.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 18:14:57</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2003-06-26] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Enters Star Wars Galaxies<span>Star Wars Galaxies: An Empire Divided is released. LOA enters this game in force, establishing the Gorath server as our home.<br><p>Posted by: Calan Adan - 2003-12-28 12:54:11</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2003-09-24] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">Greggar Becomes Team Lead for DAOC<span>Being heavily involved in the Dark Age of Camelot game and community, Greggar is promoted by Mythic to the Team Leader for Paladin's position. <br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 09:20:59</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint"><span class="specialtimepoint">[2003-11-01] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">"AVATAR" Guild Portal Goes Live<span>Needing desperately to have a guild portal solution to meet our needs, Freejack took up the challenge of programming a home-grown application called "AVATAR". Providing many tools such as news, security, roster, dynamic pages, tales and timelines, AVATAR has been a huge success for our guild. 

We hope to allow other guilds to download and install AVATAR in the near future.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-05 10:02:56</p></span></a></span></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2003-12-09] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Enters Horizons<span>A small band of Emmisarries sent forth by Brimstone reach the new world to rebuild the Tree of Life and its village.
<br><p>Posted by: Gileean Crystalthorn - 2004-01-07 13:11:22</p></span></a></div></li>
	<li><div class="timepoint">[2003-12-25] - <a href="timelines.php" onclick="return false;">LOA Donates money to RAINN organization<span>Namoric raised his hand to organize and manage our 2003 Christmas Charity event. His recommendation was the RAINN (Web site:
http://www.rainn.org) charity. Our community raised $500.00 to help those who are victims of sexual abuse and violence.<br><p>Posted by: Brimstone - 2004-01-04 19:05:55</p></span></a></div></li>
